# 🚆 Railway Reservation System

A console-based Railway Reservation System developed using **Java, JDBC, and MySQL**. This application enables users to manage train reservations efficiently through functionalities such as viewing trains, adding passengers, booking tickets, canceling tickets, and generating bills.

## 📌 Features

* View available trains and seat availability.
* Register passenger details.
* Book train tickets with booking and journey dates.
* View booked tickets.
* Cancel tickets and automatically update seat availability.
* Generate bills with fare calculation.
* MySQL database integration using JDBC.
* Modular design using separate classes for better code organization.

## 🛠 Technologies Used

* Java
* JDBC
* MySQL
* SQL
* Eclipse IDE

## 📂 Project Structure

```
RailwayReservationSystem
│
├── Main.java
├── DBConnection.java
├── TrainService.java
├── PassengerService.java
├── TicketService.java
└── BillService.java
```

## ⚙️ Functionalities

### Train Management

* Display train details.
* Show available seats and fare information.

### Passenger Management

* Add passenger details to the database.

### Ticket Booking

* Book tickets with journey and booking dates.
* Store reservation information in MySQL.

### Ticket Cancellation

* Cancel booked tickets.
* Automatically update seat availability.

### Bill Generation

* Generate detailed bills including:

  * Passenger details
  * Train details
  * Number of seats booked
  * Fare per seat
  * Total amount

## 🎯 Learning Outcomes

This project demonstrates:

* Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) concepts in Java.
* JDBC connectivity with MySQL.
* CRUD operations using SQL.
* Modular programming and code organization.
* Basic database management and reservation system design.

## 📖 About

This project was developed as a mini-project to understand Java backend development and database integration. It provides a simple simulation of a railway reservation system and serves as a foundation for building larger reservation or management systems.
